      "index": "aM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1832752277,
      "version": 247,
      "versionNonce": 1198164693,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782542251874,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Questions\n1. what if reciever sent an ack but due to an issue web socket connection lost and record in the inbox table is not deleted\nwhen user reconnects will the chat server again resends the messages?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Questions\n1. what if reciever sent an ack but due to an issue web socket connection lost and record in the inbox table is not deleted\nwhen user reconnects will the chat server again resends the messages?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "m7t-u-Fz2PIUGC0ezKsI8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 356.3080359065624,
      "y": 1568.0771899187087,
      "width": 2014.1383056640625,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2081800379,
      "version": 421,
      "versionNonce": 725068373,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782542930774,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to handle billions of request \n scale chat servers horizontally along with we use redis pub/sub, here redis pub/sub will not store data its just sends data who are online, then how we send messages who are not online we use inbox table\n\nwhy not kafka pub/sub\nfor every user we need to create a topic which is vast, because its a kafka limitation\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to handle billions of request \n scale chat servers horizontally along with we use redis pub/sub, here redis pub/sub will not store data its just sends data who are online, then how we send messages who are not online we use inbox table\n\nwhy not kafka pub/sub\nfor every user we need to create a topic which is vast, because its a kafka limitation\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
